attributes.Long form description: The student moves the controller from the console to the grip, then attaches it to the strap. They put the console on the table and turn it on, then turn it off again. They swap out the game card and SD card.

attributes.Transcription: Now please change the controller from handheld mode to the Joy-Con comfort grip.

attributes.Action sentence: The student shifts the Joy-Con controller from the Nintendo Switch to the Joy-Con comfort grip.

attributes.Transcription: You'll have to press the round button on the back of the controller and then put it upwards.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: the student press the wrong button

attributes.Transcription: The minus should be at the top.
Nice well done.
Now please change the controller from the Joy-Con comfort grip to two Joy-Cons.

attributes.Action sentence: The student mounts the Joy-Con controller onto the Joy-Con strap.

attributes.Transcription: Make sure to engage the white lock at the bottom by pressing it
Nice well done.
Now please change the controller from two Joy-Cons to hadled mode.

attributes.Action sentence: The student shifts the Joy-Con controller from the Joy-Con comfort grip to the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: You'll have to slide it in from the top.
Nice well done.
Now please stand the Nintendo Switch on the table using the kickstand.

attributes.Action sentence: The student stands the Nintendo Switch on the table using the kickstand.

attributes.Transcription: You should be able to just pull it outwards.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student keep pressing the kickstand.

attributes.Transcription: Like pull it away from the Nintendo Switch not downwards.
Nice well done.
Now please change the gamecard of the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges a game card for the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: good job.
Now please change the micro SD card on the nintendo swith.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges an SD card with the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student can't find the sd card.

attributes.Transcription: The micro SD card is under de kickstand.
Nice well done.
Now please turn on the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns on the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student accidentally remove one Joy-Con.

attributes.Transcription: Well done.
Now please turn off the Nintendo Switch again.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns off their Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: It's only in stand-by right now, you have to press the button for three seconds.
Well done
you can stop the recording now.
